Anaplastic lymphoma kinase inhibitors and their effect on the kidney.
According to the package insert and published literature, treatment with several ALK-1 inhibitors appears to be associated with the development of peripheral edema and rare electrolyte disorders, kidney failure, proteinuria and an increased risk for the development and progression of renal cysts. This review introduces the different types of ALK inhibitors, focusing on their detailed kidney-related side effects in clinical practice.
