Visit-to-visit blood pressure variability and risk of dementia in chronic kidney disease patients: why are blood pressure changes so important in cognitive functions?
Both higher systolic and diastolic BP variabilities were associated with any type of dementia, including Alzheimer's and vascular dementia. Physicians must be aware of BP variability when evaluating CKD patients with hypertension.
